Reasoning: The previous SUM formulas returned 0 because the point cells contain text strings like "3" (produced by IF formulas). In Excel/LibreOffice, SUM treats text as 0. To convert those strings to numbers we need to wrap each cell with VALUE (or use IFERROR(VALUE(...),0) to handle blanks). We'll replace the formulas in column 15 (O) with a SUM that applies VALUE to each point cell:  
`=SUM(VALUE(Fr),VALUE(Hr),VALUE(Jr),VALUE(Lr),VALUE(Nr),VALUE(Tr),VALUE(Vr),VALUE(Xr))`  
where *r* is the row number. We'll also unmerge any merged cells in column 15, save, recalculate, and verify a few totals.
